Date: Mon, 25 May 1998 12:20:20 -0500 (CDT)
From: Dr.Ron Worley <rworley@texas.net>

Though superficially laudable, the idea of debt forgiveness for African
countries who seemingly have no concept of population control, economics,
sanitation, and civilized discourse is sadly misguided. It will simply
continue the cycle of taking aid and loans for necessary development and
spending it for weapons, palaces and planes for the thugs in power.
What lessons do you teach when irresponsibility is tacitly encouraged?
--
Dr.Ron Worley
e-mail: rworley@texas.net
